# Types & Constants Separation

TSX files are for UI only. Do not declare `interface`, `type`, or module-level `const` data in `.tsx` files.

## Folder layout

```
types/
  landing.types.ts      # all landing page interfaces
  shared.types.ts       # all shared component interfaces
  contact.types.ts      # one file per page/domain (add as needed)
constants/
  landing.constants.ts  # all landing page constants (same grouping)
  shared.constants.ts
```

- **One `.types.ts` file per page or domain** — not one file per component.
- Group related interfaces inside that file (hero, problem section, etc.) with a short comment.
- Prefer **`interface`** for object/props shapes; use `type` only for unions, aliases, or mapped types.

## What goes where

| Artifact | Location | Example |
|----------|----------|---------|
| Props, config shapes | `types/<domain>.types.ts` | `HeroPrimaryCtaProps`, `DesktopCardConfig` |
| Static data, class strings | `constants/<domain>.constants.ts` | `DESKTOP_CARDS`, `NAV_LINK_CLASS_NAME` |
| Component markup & hooks | `*.tsx` | `ProblemSection.tsx` |

## TSX rules

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — interfaces/constants in TSX
interface FooProps { id: string }
const ITEMS = [{ label: 'A' }] as const;
export function Foo({ id }: FooProps) { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — import from domain modules
import type { FooProps } from '@/types/landing.types';
import { ITEMS } from '@/constants/landing.constants';
export function Foo({ id }: FooProps) { ... }
```

## Naming

- Types file: `<domain>.types.ts` — export `PascalCase` interfaces (`HeroPrimaryCtaProps`, `DesktopCardConfig`).
- Constants file: `<domain>.constants.ts` — use `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` for exported constants.
- Section comments inside a types file, e.g. `/** Landing page — problem section */`.

## Exceptions

- Config/build scripts (`playwright.config.ts`, `next.config.ts`) and generated files (`tokens/build/*`).
- Test files may define local fixtures inline.
